On Thu, Nov 24, 2011 at 3:10 AM, John Anderson <wvukidsdoc(-at-)yahoo.com> wrote:

> Mike, gone over many times, really as mentioned only trivial issues.
>
> Breather, get the vanagon one (they are a bit uncommon now days cause the
> clip that holds it down
> likes to crack off) and you are fine, hose can be forced right onto it.
>
> Dipstick, get the vanagon one and no issue at all, you just have dual
> dipsticks when you transfer
> your assembly, both are easily readable, you can decide which you feel is
> more accurate.
>
> Not mentioned that I see, M10 motor mount holes on the vanagon block, M8
> on the '79.  Drill out
> the holes in your mounts, takes 5 minutes, and I feel that you need 4
> shorter bolts, any good hardware
> store can provide.
>
> He may or may not have '79 heads, such a thing does exist, but doesn't
> matter anyway, valve
> sizes do change trivially, but doesn't matter one bit if they are '79, OEM
> Vanagon, or AMC replacements,
> all will function just fine with your ancillaries.  Hopefully they are a
> matched set on the engine at
> least would be all I'd look for.
>
> Nothing to this swap into a '79, just unbolt all the FI, tinwork,
> alternator, etc, etc from yours bolt it onto
> his.  Compared to putting it into a '72-'78 this is a joke.  All new FI
> hoses while you are at it, and new
> or rebuilt injectors make sense.
>
> John
>
>
